        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 18 at 3:15PM EDT by NWS Grand Rapids MI</headline>
        <description>At 315 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles northwest of Farwell, or 12 miles northwest of Clare, moving
south at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Clare...               Farwell...             Windover Lake...
Five Lakes...          Doc and Tom Lake...    Lily Lake...
Lake George...         Eight Point Lake...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
